The paper deals with processing sensor data and specifically focuses on background subtraction, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a method for updating the singular vectors in a computationally efficient manner, which suggests that it may be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper involves iterative computations and optimization, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT).
